1
00:00:14,480 --> 00:00:17,440
♪In the airport lounge
at the break of day♪

2
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:22,200
♪A page of dust beneath my fingers♪

3
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:25,160
♪Filled with stories♪

4
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:28,280
♪That others never got to tell♪

5
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,960
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

6
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,600
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

7
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,160
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

8
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:40,040
♪The world is split an inch wider♪

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,600
♪Raise your eyes, face the light♪

10
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:45,080
♪See the truth, and see the fright♪

11
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,800
♪Guard the crack within this door♪

12
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:52,600
♪Keep the way back home
always burning bright♪

13
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:57,040
♪The camera pans
across the boarding crowd♪

14
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,200
♪Some wear a smile,
some have their eyes adrift♪

15
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:01,360
♪A red suitcase♪

16
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:05,360
♪Tied with faded pasts
and broken prayers♪

17
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:09,360
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

18
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:12,080
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

19
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:13,960
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

20
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:17,400
♪It's the heartbeat
echoing the call of law♪

21
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
[Gimlet Eyes]

22
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:32,960
[Episode 13]

23
00:01:34,840 --> 00:01:35,950
[Trending: 'Luxury Watch' Remark
by Binhai Huayan Airport Customs Staff]

24
00:01:35,950 --> 00:01:36,380
Recently,

25
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:37,290
a video

26
00:01:37,310 --> 00:01:39,410
about Binhai Huayan Airport Customs

27
00:01:39,430 --> 00:01:40,380
shot to the top of trending.

28
00:01:40,510 --> 00:01:43,290
What the officer said
in the video set the internet off.

29
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:44,770
This watch.

30
00:01:46,640 --> 00:01:47,210
Three hundred thousand.

31
00:01:47,310 --> 00:01:48,290
Her salary?

32
00:01:48,640 --> 00:01:49,410
In one month,

33
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:51,620
she could probably buy dozens of those.

34
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:55,130
This year's Richard Mille
limited collector's edition,

35
00:01:55,480 --> 00:01:57,460
serial number 001, worth 800,000 euros.

36
00:01:57,480 --> 00:01:58,570
It passed through
this gentleman's hands.

37
00:01:58,590 --> 00:01:59,460
Dabao,

38
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:00,380
what's

39
00:02:00,400 --> 00:02:01,540
so funny?

40
00:02:02,560 --> 00:02:04,620
Look at these trolls.

41
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:06,210
They're tearing Customs apart.

42
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:09,170
That entertaining?

43
00:02:09,470 --> 00:02:10,690
More entertaining than me?

44
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:15,540
You and those comments?
Both my finest work.

45
00:02:15,750 --> 00:02:16,690
Can't choose.

46
00:02:17,960 --> 00:02:19,980
If there's anything you want,
just say the word.

47
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,570
I'm in a good mood. Let's go shopping.

48
00:02:21,630 --> 00:02:22,660
Seriously, Dabao?

49
00:02:22,680 --> 00:02:23,450
Of course.

50
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:24,780
Great!

51
00:02:24,910 --> 00:02:25,850
Thank you!

52
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:28,010
Seatbelt.

53
00:02:33,750 --> 00:02:35,060
Where'd this necklace come from?

54
00:02:35,630 --> 00:02:36,410
Xiaoyan,

55
00:02:36,840 --> 00:02:37,890
what's wrong with you?

56
00:02:38,190 --> 00:02:39,890
Don't talk to your father like that.

57
00:02:40,430 --> 00:02:42,290
Do you know what people say about me

58
00:02:42,310 --> 00:02:43,450
because of this necklace?

59
00:02:43,470 --> 00:02:44,130
They say

60
00:02:44,150 --> 00:02:45,820
there's no way
a customs officer could afford it.

61
00:02:45,910 --> 00:02:47,260
That I must've dodged customs duties.

62
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:49,380
Nonsense.

63
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:50,820
Your father bought it

64
00:02:50,840 --> 00:02:53,060
from an overseas auction site.

65
00:02:53,680 --> 00:02:55,780
It's all legal.

66
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:59,100
Mom, Dad…

67
00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:01,450
you really screwed me over this time.

68
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:02,570
What happened?

69
00:03:02,590 --> 00:03:03,570
Why are you crying?

70
00:03:04,190 --> 00:03:05,340
Hey, don't cry, sweetheart…

71
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:07,890
There's no way I can clear my name now.

72
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:09,450
Come on, don't cry.

73
00:03:09,910 --> 00:03:10,980
We knew

74
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,540
how much you loved that necklace.

75
00:03:12,560 --> 00:03:14,380
So when we saw it on the site that day,

76
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:15,980
your dad just bought it.

77
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:17,890
We'd never have done it if we had known

78
00:03:17,910 --> 00:03:19,450
it would cause you this much trouble.

79
00:03:19,470 --> 00:03:21,380
Mom, that's not the point.

80
00:03:23,470 --> 00:03:24,220
Lyu,

81
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:25,730
talk to her.

82
00:03:25,750 --> 00:03:26,940
Look at her, she's a mess.

83
00:03:27,870 --> 00:03:29,690
Then quit your job at customs.

84
00:03:31,310 --> 00:03:32,170
Why should I?

85
00:03:32,630 --> 00:03:34,170
Why should I quit my job?

86
00:03:34,590 --> 00:03:37,100
I told you to come work
at my company after graduation.

87
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:38,690
But you just had to go into customs.

88
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:40,290
Making such lousy money,

89
00:03:40,310 --> 00:03:41,890
living on your own for over a year,

90
00:03:42,080 --> 00:03:43,730
running yourself ragged every day,

91
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:44,850
feeling exhausted…

92
00:03:44,870 --> 00:03:46,450
Are you done messing around?

93
00:03:46,910 --> 00:03:48,260
I am not messing around.

94
00:03:48,590 --> 00:03:50,610
I take my job at customs seriously.

95
00:03:50,630 --> 00:03:52,060
Then quit whining

96
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:53,220
about nothing.

97
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:55,540
Nothing?

98
00:03:55,560 --> 00:03:57,500
This is about our reputation!

99
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:02,730
Forget it.

100
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:04,130
I've got nothing to hide.

101
00:04:04,150 --> 00:04:06,170
They can trash me all they want.
I'm not afraid of it.

102
00:04:06,470 --> 00:04:07,410
I'll clear

103
00:04:07,430 --> 00:04:08,890
our section's name myself.

104
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:11,980
Also,

105
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,340
I won't quit this job.

106
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:14,730
I'm staying.

107
00:04:15,030 --> 00:04:16,100
Starting today,

108
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:17,900
I'll be living in the dorm.

109
00:04:18,830 --> 00:04:19,100
Wait,

110
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:20,980
you're moving into the dorm?

111
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:22,780
Lyu,

112
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:25,100
she's moving out.

113
00:04:25,120 --> 00:04:26,250
Aren't you gonna say anything?

114
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:28,020
Let her learn the hard way.

115
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:31,460
If she can really
prove herself at customs,

116
00:04:31,830 --> 00:04:32,730
that's not a bad thing.

117
00:04:34,480 --> 00:04:35,290
Xiaoyan!

118
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:36,540
Oh, come on!

119
00:04:36,870 --> 00:04:37,610
Xiaoyan,

120
00:04:37,950 --> 00:04:38,980
what's wrong?

121
00:04:39,870 --> 00:04:40,610
Xiaoyan!

122
00:04:41,880 --> 00:04:43,660
Zhang Yu, are you okay?

123
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:45,820
Netizens are really
coming down hard on you guys.

124
00:04:45,880 --> 00:04:47,820
I'm okay, Jing.

125
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:50,610
They just don't know the full story.

126
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:53,810
I've already braced myself for this.

127
00:04:54,440 --> 00:04:56,810
Don't worry.
The truth speaks for itself.

128
00:04:59,640 --> 00:05:02,180
It's tough being in your line of work.

129
00:05:02,320 --> 00:05:03,730
One minute you're praised,

130
00:05:03,790 --> 00:05:05,210
the next you're getting slammed.

131
00:05:05,390 --> 00:05:07,210
But I know that's not who you are.

132
00:05:08,110 --> 00:05:08,890
Yeah.

133
00:05:08,910 --> 00:05:10,980
As long as you believe me,
that's enough.

134
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:13,730
Well…

135
00:05:14,110 --> 00:05:15,660
If it really gets too much,

136
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:17,730
you can quit.

137
00:05:18,430 --> 00:05:19,300
That translation job

138
00:05:19,320 --> 00:05:20,810
I mentioned last time is still open.

139
00:05:20,830 --> 00:05:21,900
You can join anytime.

140
00:05:22,390 --> 00:05:23,620
Thanks, Jing.

141
00:05:23,790 --> 00:05:25,450
But you know me.

142
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:27,410
I'm tough.

143
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:28,900
I thrive under pressure.

144
00:05:28,960 --> 00:05:29,730
Don't worry.

145
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:31,050
Who is it?

146
00:05:42,390 --> 00:05:43,490
What's going on?

147
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:44,540
You scared me.

148
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:45,220
Yu,

149
00:05:45,510 --> 00:05:46,740
from today on,

150
00:05:47,590 --> 00:05:48,620
I'm staying here with you.

151
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:50,650
I've moved out, and I'm not going back.

152
00:06:00,070 --> 00:06:01,290
Fought with your parents again?

153
00:06:04,070 --> 00:06:04,700
Yu,

154
00:06:05,280 --> 00:06:06,900
sorry for all the trouble
I've caused you and Mr. Guo.

155
00:06:08,670 --> 00:06:09,700
It's fine.

156
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:11,620
With things blowing up like this,

157
00:06:11,640 --> 00:06:13,340
they'd still come at us

158
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,460
even without that necklace.

159
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:16,850
People online these days…

160
00:06:16,870 --> 00:06:17,980
They make stuff up in seconds,

161
00:06:18,120 --> 00:06:19,260
and we spend forever fixing it.

162
00:06:19,280 --> 00:06:21,050
How can they just believe
anything they're told?

163
00:06:21,070 --> 00:06:22,210
No facts, no thinking, nothing.

164
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:24,340
No…

165
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:26,050
I need to push back on this.

166
00:06:26,790 --> 00:06:28,050
Enough.

167
00:06:29,230 --> 00:06:30,130
I can't just let it go.

168
00:06:31,150 --> 00:06:32,740
Check this out, people.

169
00:06:32,760 --> 00:06:34,930
A new video about customs
just got posted.

170
00:06:35,640 --> 00:06:36,260
"The Truth!

171
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:37,900
Taken down by customs instantly."

172
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:43,410
Recently,

173
00:06:44,030 --> 00:06:45,490
a video from an unknown source

174
00:06:45,510 --> 00:06:46,740
started circulating online.

175
00:06:47,150 --> 00:06:49,410
In the footage,
a customs officer is seen

176
00:06:49,870 --> 00:06:51,700
slipping into a customs warehouse,

177
00:06:52,030 --> 00:06:54,820
putting a high-end Richard Mille watch
into his own pocket…

178
00:06:56,280 --> 00:06:57,500
What is wrong with these people?

179
00:06:57,590 --> 00:06:58,780
Are they serious?

180
00:06:59,350 --> 00:07:01,700
The incident happened last night.

181
00:07:02,030 --> 00:07:03,850
And the video's already out today.

182
00:07:06,840 --> 00:07:07,890
Feels like

183
00:07:08,870 --> 00:07:10,890
this whole thing is aimed at my mentor.

184
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:15,590
[Zhang's Shantou Rice Noodles]

185
00:07:15,590 --> 00:07:16,570
[Zhang's Shantou Rice Noodles]
Bye, Zhang.

186
00:07:17,120 --> 00:07:17,780
[Zhang's Shantou Rice Noodles]
Take care!

187
00:07:17,840 --> 00:07:18,450
[Zhang's Shantou Rice Noodles]
Come back anytime!

188
00:07:18,470 --> 00:07:19,260
[Zhang's Shantou Rice Noodles]
Will do.

189
00:07:19,470 --> 00:07:19,820
[Zhang's Shantou Rice Noodles]
Alright.

190
00:07:20,190 --> 00:07:20,610
[Zhang's Shantou Rice Noodles]
Uncle Xiang,

191
00:07:20,610 --> 00:07:21,280
[Zhang's Shantou Rice Noodles]

192
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:23,100
this place is incredible.

193
00:07:23,350 --> 00:07:24,220
I'm stuffed.

194
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:25,290
How'd you even find it?

195
00:07:25,430 --> 00:07:26,540
You know me.

196
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:28,290
Always out with a camera.

197
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:30,450
I just stumbled on it.

198
00:07:30,470 --> 00:07:31,850
I tend to spot places

199
00:07:31,870 --> 00:07:33,570
most people would miss.

200
00:07:34,190 --> 00:07:35,100
I envy that.

201
00:07:35,430 --> 00:07:37,540
You really know this city,
always out exploring,

202
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:39,850
meeting all kinds of people.

203
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:43,450
They're out.

204
00:07:48,510 --> 00:07:49,220
Look,

205
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:50,490
everyone on this street

206
00:07:50,950 --> 00:07:53,370
has their own unique story.

207
00:07:53,600 --> 00:07:55,540
What if the story is shady,

208
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:56,980
dark, or even twisted?

209
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:57,810
Will you listen to it?

210
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:01,930
Life comes in all kinds of shades.

211
00:08:02,070 --> 00:08:04,660
People are all different.

212
00:08:04,680 --> 00:08:05,140
Right?

213
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:07,050
I can't really deal with that.

214
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:08,730
However,

215
00:08:08,750 --> 00:08:10,290
I'd love to hear your story.

216
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:13,580
By the way… Did you take me out today

217
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:16,460
because my mom asked you to check on me?

218
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:18,700
She saw those videos online.

219
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:23,020
That video is clearly aimed at you.

220
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:25,250
And the one about the doll
before that, too.

221
00:08:25,630 --> 00:08:27,340
How could your mom and I not worry?

222
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:28,700
You're in the same position

223
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:30,490
Chen used to be in.

224
00:08:30,630 --> 00:08:33,340
If anything goes wrong, you'll be
the first in the line of fire.

225
00:08:34,870 --> 00:08:35,770
You expect us to just

226
00:08:35,790 --> 00:08:37,460
sit there and watch you take the hit?

227
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:39,530
It's just a video.

228
00:08:39,550 --> 00:08:40,770
It won't bite.

229
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:43,580
What concerns me is not the video,

230
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:45,340
it's whoever's behind it.

231
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:47,530
Whoever's behind it

232
00:08:47,670 --> 00:08:48,580
won't get far.

233
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:49,610
We'll catch them.

234
00:08:49,790 --> 00:08:50,850
I don't care about that.

235
00:08:50,870 --> 00:08:52,100
Just make sure you stay safe.

236
00:08:52,480 --> 00:08:53,610
I'll be fine.

237
00:08:53,870 --> 00:08:54,490
Alright.

238
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:56,490
Enough of this.

239
00:08:56,510 --> 00:08:56,940
Come on.

240
00:08:57,360 --> 00:09:00,180
Let's go take a walk.

241
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:03,300
Don't follow them.

242
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:05,010
No?

243
00:09:09,510 --> 00:09:11,610
That old man looks familiar.

244
00:09:13,870 --> 00:09:15,340
Remember the photography exhibit?

245
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:17,980
Yeah, that's him.

246
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:21,010
Those two…

247
00:09:21,390 --> 00:09:22,890
He might know Guo Cong.

248
00:09:23,630 --> 00:09:25,820
But I don't think he has
anything to do with customs.

249
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:43,770
Guo,

250
00:09:44,630 --> 00:09:45,770
I've decided.

251
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:47,850
I need to figure out

252
00:09:48,030 --> 00:09:50,490
a way to get Cong out of Customs.

253
00:09:52,670 --> 00:09:54,010
Well, this is on me.

254
00:09:54,030 --> 00:09:55,700
I should've stopped him back then.

255
00:09:56,960 --> 00:09:58,610
Now that Chen's retired,

256
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:01,060
the kid's taken his place.

257
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:03,530
He's basically become everyone's target.

258
00:10:03,790 --> 00:10:05,220
That worries me.

259
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:06,420
Guo,

260
00:10:08,670 --> 00:10:10,850
he's going to have to
take a hit for now.

261
00:10:12,390 --> 00:10:13,340
I'll at least

262
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:15,490
transfer him off Passenger Inspection.

263
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:17,060
Don't worry.

264
00:10:17,790 --> 00:10:19,530
I'll look after him.

265
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:20,530
Oh,

266
00:10:20,870 --> 00:10:21,940
and one more thing,

267
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:25,220
I had dinner with him the other day.

268
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:29,610
He said he envies
how I'm always out exploring.

269
00:10:32,480 --> 00:10:33,890
Made me pretty happy.

270
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:37,300
And then I thought,

271
00:10:38,750 --> 00:10:40,650
if I can really get him

272
00:10:40,670 --> 00:10:42,420
out of customs,

273
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:44,530
I'll shut down this company,

274
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:46,700
hand it over to someone else,

275
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:49,370
and take him traveling the world.

276
00:10:49,870 --> 00:10:51,980
Be a real explorer for once.

277
00:10:55,550 --> 00:10:56,530
Guo,

278
00:10:58,200 --> 00:10:59,340
wish me luck.

279
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:05,890
This is driving me crazy.

280
00:11:05,910 --> 00:11:08,180
These past couple of years,
it's all these paid posts,

281
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:10,420
people stirring things up online
with an agenda.

282
00:11:10,550 --> 00:11:11,730
Bowen, look at this.

283
00:11:11,910 --> 00:11:13,530
Our smiles aren't up to standard.

284
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:14,530
Our service lacks warmth.

285
00:11:14,550 --> 00:11:16,340
Our enforcement isn't proper

286
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:17,180
and lacks transparency.

287
00:11:17,630 --> 00:11:19,580
It's the same thing over and over,

288
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:21,530
trying to pit the public against us.

289
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:24,250
And the worst part is,
some people just buy into it.

290
00:11:24,270 --> 00:11:25,220
They read

291
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:26,770
a few made-up posts online,

292
00:11:26,910 --> 00:11:28,300
and suddenly they're outraged at us.

293
00:11:28,550 --> 00:11:29,980
And Mr. Guo.

294
00:11:30,150 --> 00:11:32,250
He led several major cases,

295
00:11:32,790 --> 00:11:35,010
so now smugglers see him as a threat.

296
00:11:35,790 --> 00:11:37,770
Every time someone tries
to smear customs,

297
00:11:37,790 --> 00:11:39,130
his name comes up.

298
00:11:39,440 --> 00:11:41,130
And he's the Section Director,

299
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,490
which makes him a sitting target.

300
00:11:42,910 --> 00:11:44,370
Attacks are coming from everywhere.

301
00:11:44,550 --> 00:11:46,130
We can't even cover for him.

302
00:11:46,670 --> 00:11:48,180
Well, next time I need your cover,

303
00:11:48,270 --> 00:11:49,490
I'll give you a heads-up.

304
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:51,890
Wait, are you still smiling?

305
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:54,060
What, should I be crying?

306
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:55,340
You said it yourself,

307
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:56,580
it's not the first time.

308
00:11:56,790 --> 00:11:58,130
The more they try to throw us off,

309
00:11:58,150 --> 00:11:59,420
the more we need to stay sharp.

310
00:11:59,870 --> 00:12:02,300
As long as we hold the line,
we won't be beaten.

311
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:04,220
Open or hidden,

312
00:12:04,270 --> 00:12:05,130
they can't touch us.

313
00:12:05,550 --> 00:12:06,180
Am I right?

314
00:12:07,670 --> 00:12:08,820
Hello, this way, please.

315
00:12:16,550 --> 00:12:17,730
Hey, look at those two.

316
00:12:18,030 --> 00:12:19,370
I think I've seen them online.

317
00:12:19,870 --> 00:12:21,130
Yeah, you're right.

318
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:21,890
I think it's them.

319
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:22,890
Let me see.

320
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:26,220
It does look like them.

321
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:27,940
Yeah, check this out.

322
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:29,770
Excuse me,

323
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:32,100
no photos or video recording allowed.

324
00:12:32,120 --> 00:12:33,100
Please put your phone away.

325
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:34,650
What's the problem, officer?

326
00:12:34,670 --> 00:12:36,460
We can't even take a selfie?

327
00:12:36,480 --> 00:12:37,180
Yeah.

328
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:38,650
Anything involving the inspection lanes

329
00:12:38,670 --> 00:12:40,370
or on-duty officers isn't allowed.

330
00:12:40,870 --> 00:12:41,250
Come on,

331
00:12:41,510 --> 00:12:43,220
there are videos of you
all over the internet.

332
00:12:43,240 --> 00:12:44,180
Why can't we

333
00:12:44,200 --> 00:12:45,820
just take a picture?

334
00:12:45,840 --> 00:12:47,530
Those are from non-restricted areas.

335
00:12:48,510 --> 00:12:50,890
People are free to discuss
or share what they want.

336
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:52,700
But making baseless accusations

337
00:12:52,720 --> 00:12:54,250
can lead to legal consequences.

338
00:12:56,510 --> 00:12:57,370
Wow, that's scary.

339
00:12:57,390 --> 00:12:59,250
I took their photo.
And I'm going to jail.

340
00:12:59,480 --> 00:13:00,730
They're famous now.

341
00:13:00,750 --> 00:13:01,730
Way above us, huh?

342
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:02,940
Look,

343
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:04,610
everything I say and do

344
00:13:04,630 --> 00:13:06,850
is being recorded by this body cam.

345
00:13:07,510 --> 00:13:09,460
I'm trying to resolve this rationally.

346
00:13:09,630 --> 00:13:11,250
If it escalates into obstruction,

347
00:13:11,320 --> 00:13:13,300
it could affect your future travel.

348
00:13:13,840 --> 00:13:14,460
Go ahead.

349
00:13:14,480 --> 00:13:15,420
- Film me then. - Come on.

350
00:13:15,440 --> 00:13:16,180
- Film me. - Drop it.

351
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:17,420
- What? - They're doing their job.

352
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:18,580
I just took a picture.

353
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:19,700
They've seized people's stuff before!

354
00:13:30,030 --> 00:13:30,650
Come in.

355
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:32,980
Yan Bowen,

356
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:35,300
what's the occasion?

357
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:37,130
Why the sudden hot pot invite?

358
00:13:37,910 --> 00:13:40,180
You all looked pretty worn out today.

359
00:13:40,960 --> 00:13:42,650
We're worn out every day.

360
00:13:42,670 --> 00:13:43,820
Why today, specifically?

361
00:13:45,790 --> 00:13:47,700
What did you do

362
00:13:47,720 --> 00:13:48,700
that you're not telling us?

363
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:49,940
Nothing.

364
00:13:50,080 --> 00:13:51,980
Enough, Xiaoyan, stop messing with him.

365
00:13:52,030 --> 00:13:53,220
Hot pot's nice.

366
00:13:53,390 --> 00:13:55,820
There's nothing
a good hot pot can't fix,

367
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:57,980
and if it doesn't,
just go for another round.

368
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:58,530
Right?

369
00:14:00,390 --> 00:14:02,820
But these are basically

370
00:14:03,080 --> 00:14:04,890
all Xiaoyan's favorites, aren't they?

371
00:14:06,030 --> 00:14:06,530
Well,

372
00:14:06,630 --> 00:14:08,580
daikon, oyster mushrooms…

373
00:14:08,670 --> 00:14:10,490
You like those too, don't you?

374
00:14:10,630 --> 00:14:11,130
Yeah,

375
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:12,420
but all you got for me

376
00:14:12,480 --> 00:14:15,010
is daikon and mushrooms?

377
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:18,700
Yu, um… you…

378
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:19,650
what else do you want?

379
00:14:19,670 --> 00:14:20,580
I'll go get it right now.

380
00:14:20,840 --> 00:14:21,220
Stop it.

381
00:14:21,240 --> 00:14:22,130
- Stop teasing him.
- You don't even know

382
00:14:22,150 --> 00:14:23,060
what I like.

383
00:14:23,080 --> 00:14:24,300
You told me not to tease him,

384
00:14:24,320 --> 00:14:25,850
now you're dragging me into it too?

385
00:14:25,870 --> 00:14:27,770
You two, come give me a hand with this.

386
00:14:27,790 --> 00:14:28,530
- Go. - Go.

387
00:14:28,630 --> 00:14:30,300
I'm not going. All I get is veggies.

388
00:14:30,320 --> 00:14:31,010
Not interested.

389
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:32,250
Which one?

390
00:14:32,270 --> 00:14:33,180
Just grab whatever.

391
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:33,730
Alright.

392
00:14:33,790 --> 00:14:34,370
Let's go.

393
00:14:37,270 --> 00:14:37,940
Come on, sit.

394
00:14:40,790 --> 00:14:41,250
Here.

395
00:14:42,480 --> 00:14:44,100
Water's boiling. Put the meat in.

396
00:14:44,100 --> 00:14:49,440
[Customs Dormitory]

397
00:14:58,270 --> 00:14:59,010
Xiaoyan,

398
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:01,340
Miss Princess,

399
00:15:01,360 --> 00:15:02,700
you just ate, and you're already gaming?

400
00:15:03,200 --> 00:15:04,340
I'm just…

401
00:15:04,510 --> 00:15:05,850
I ate way too much.

402
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:07,180
Blame Yan Bowen.

403
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:08,940
He bought everything I like.

404
00:15:09,080 --> 00:15:10,420
I've gotta move a bit, burn it off.

405
00:15:13,670 --> 00:15:15,180
Yu, you don't have to help.

406
00:15:15,200 --> 00:15:16,180
Let me do it.

407
00:15:16,200 --> 00:15:17,100
It's fine.

408
00:15:17,120 --> 00:15:19,180
I can't just eat and walk away.

409
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:20,300
I'm not a freeloader.

410
00:15:20,960 --> 00:15:21,730
Don't bait me.

411
00:15:21,750 --> 00:15:23,610
I'm in the middle of a match here.

412
00:15:24,550 --> 00:15:26,700
Where's the route?

413
00:15:42,510 --> 00:15:43,340
Look at this.

414
00:15:43,440 --> 00:15:45,650
We've explained it.
Why don't they believe us?

415
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:47,370
That official statement we released

416
00:15:47,390 --> 00:15:48,820
only got a dozen comments,

417
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:50,580
and none of them really cared.

418
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:51,850
Most people

419
00:15:51,870 --> 00:15:54,180
just go for the sensational stuff.

420
00:15:54,320 --> 00:15:56,460
And some just want to stir things up.

421
00:15:56,550 --> 00:15:58,490
They don't care about the truth.

422
00:15:59,240 --> 00:15:59,890
Yeah…

423
00:15:59,910 --> 00:16:01,730
that's how it is online.

424
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:04,730
Nobody reads clear, factual statements

425
00:16:04,790 --> 00:16:06,610
from official sources

426
00:16:06,630 --> 00:16:07,580
because they have no drama.

427
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:10,850
But clickbait headlines

428
00:16:10,870 --> 00:16:12,580
and twisted stories

429
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:13,980
get all the attention.

430
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:14,980
That's not okay.

431
00:16:15,120 --> 00:16:16,490
I can't let the truth get buried.

432
00:16:24,150 --> 00:16:25,460
Why does it have to be like this?

433
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:29,220
Didn't your supervisor tell you
to be more cautious?

434
00:16:29,240 --> 00:16:30,610
Just ignore it.

435
00:16:30,790 --> 00:16:32,980
But we can't just let people
smear us like that.

436
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:34,180
Did you see what they say?

437
00:16:34,200 --> 00:16:35,010
It's awful.

438
00:16:35,120 --> 00:16:37,530
Don't dwell on it.

439
00:16:37,550 --> 00:16:38,220
Okay?

440
00:16:38,390 --> 00:16:40,890
Ignoring it won't make it go away.

441
00:16:40,910 --> 00:16:42,130
That's just lying to yourself.

442
00:16:42,870 --> 00:16:44,460
Sometimes staying quiet

443
00:16:44,480 --> 00:16:45,980
is the best move.

444
00:16:46,150 --> 00:16:47,180
Just some public opinion.

445
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:50,340
Don't read too much into it.

446
00:16:50,360 --> 00:16:51,730
Come help us clean up.

447
00:16:51,750 --> 00:16:53,100
And then let's get some sleep.

448
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:54,130
I think it'll be fine.

449
00:16:54,670 --> 00:16:56,300
They don't know who I am anyway.

450
00:17:04,790 --> 00:17:05,730
Oh, Bowen,

451
00:17:06,240 --> 00:17:09,460
has customs always gotten
this kind of hate online?

452
00:17:10,030 --> 00:17:11,010
All the time.

453
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:12,860
When a traveler has a bad experience,

454
00:17:13,160 --> 00:17:15,250
they go online
and call people out by name.

455
00:17:16,070 --> 00:17:18,140
And if it involves a celebrity
or an influencer,

456
00:17:18,160 --> 00:17:20,700
their fans pile on too.

457
00:17:21,510 --> 00:17:22,530
But my mentor

458
00:17:22,550 --> 00:17:24,380
doesn't seem affected at all.

459
00:17:25,680 --> 00:17:26,620
You mean Mr. Guo?

460
00:17:26,920 --> 00:17:28,010
He's used to it.

461
00:17:28,640 --> 00:17:30,180
He always says,
"The truth speaks for itself."

462
00:17:30,310 --> 00:17:31,770
So all that noise

463
00:17:31,790 --> 00:17:33,220
doesn't get to him.

464
00:17:33,240 --> 00:17:34,420
He's learned to tune it out.

465
00:17:39,070 --> 00:17:40,180
They're way out of line!

466
00:17:40,720 --> 00:17:42,090
What is this even supposed to mean?

467
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:43,420
What happened?

468
00:17:56,860 --> 00:17:57,760
Oh my god.

469
00:18:01,310 --> 00:18:02,380
This is insane.

470
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:04,290
Xiaoyan, don't take it personally…

471
00:18:04,310 --> 00:18:05,810
What even is this?

472
00:18:05,830 --> 00:18:06,620
Why would they say that?

473
00:18:06,640 --> 00:18:07,770
They don't even know me.

474
00:18:08,720 --> 00:18:09,380
Let me see.

475
00:18:15,280 --> 00:18:16,400
[Don't follow the herd. See the truth.
Binhai Huayan Airport Customs]

476
00:18:16,400 --> 00:18:17,280
[Binhai Huayan Customs Officers
Video Incident Update]

477
00:18:21,720 --> 00:18:22,490
Xiaoyan.

478
00:18:24,110 --> 00:18:24,730
Xiaoyan.

479
00:18:25,350 --> 00:18:26,770
You…you're

480
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:28,620
Strawberry Jam?

481
00:18:29,790 --> 00:18:31,050
Yeah, that's me. So what?

482
00:18:31,350 --> 00:18:33,090
I stand by who I am.

483
00:18:33,160 --> 00:18:34,290
I've got nothing to hide.

484
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:35,220
They're just

485
00:18:35,240 --> 00:18:37,180
digging up stuff
from before I joined customs.

486
00:18:37,350 --> 00:18:38,660
So what? I didn't hurt anyone.

487
00:18:38,680 --> 00:18:40,010
Who hasn't been a kid before?

488
00:18:43,030 --> 00:18:44,090
Actually…

489
00:18:44,160 --> 00:18:45,620
I'm one of your followers.

490
00:18:46,640 --> 00:18:47,420
Wait, what?

491
00:18:48,510 --> 00:18:49,460
You're her…

492
00:18:49,480 --> 00:18:52,090
I follow Xiaoyan on Weibo.

493
00:18:52,240 --> 00:18:53,940
I once saw someone online

494
00:18:54,160 --> 00:18:55,980
speaking up for customs.

495
00:18:56,110 --> 00:18:57,050
Thought it was pretty cool,

496
00:18:57,070 --> 00:18:57,900
so I followed her.

497
00:18:57,920 --> 00:19:00,220
Never thought it was you.

498
00:19:00,400 --> 00:19:01,220
Strawberry Jam.

499
00:19:01,640 --> 00:19:03,980
Th-then what's your username?

500
00:19:04,510 --> 00:19:05,660
I go by…

501
00:19:06,110 --> 00:19:09,010
Breeze & Moon.

502
00:19:09,160 --> 00:19:10,860
Breeze…

503
00:19:12,480 --> 00:19:14,420
You're Breeze & Moon?

504
00:19:16,440 --> 00:19:18,220
I always thought

505
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:19,980
you were a guy in his forties

506
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:21,660
or some grandpa.

507
00:19:22,550 --> 00:19:24,290
Honestly… it kind of suits you.

508
00:19:24,310 --> 00:19:25,900
Your username suits you too!

509
00:19:26,070 --> 00:19:26,860
Are you saying

510
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:29,010
I'm immature?

511
00:19:32,480 --> 00:19:33,770
You're not.

512
00:19:34,510 --> 00:19:35,330
Not anymore.

513
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:37,620
The real immature ones

514
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:39,460
are those trashing you
behind their screens.

515
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:40,290
You're…

516
00:19:40,750 --> 00:19:42,810
stronger than all of them.

517
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:45,940
You…

518
00:19:46,310 --> 00:19:47,250
Don't comfort me.

519
00:19:47,270 --> 00:19:48,290
I don't need it.

520
00:19:48,880 --> 00:19:49,530
Well,

521
00:19:49,680 --> 00:19:50,900
just hear me out.

522
00:19:51,750 --> 00:19:52,810
I give two words:

523
00:19:53,310 --> 00:19:53,900
log off.

524
00:19:56,310 --> 00:19:57,620
That's not running away.

525
00:19:57,760 --> 00:19:59,420
It's just giving yourself some peace.

526
00:20:27,040 --> 00:20:29,090
You don't trust official statements,

527
00:20:29,440 --> 00:20:30,010
but you believe

528
00:20:30,030 --> 00:20:32,380
some blurry, random clip
from who knows where.

529
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:33,530
The blogger isn't misled.

530
00:20:33,750 --> 00:20:34,900
You are.

531
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:37,050
She used this space as her own corner,

532
00:20:37,270 --> 00:20:39,980
documenting her growth over the years.

533
00:20:40,070 --> 00:20:41,570
Yet you're digging up things

534
00:20:41,590 --> 00:20:42,980
she said years ago to judge her.

535
00:20:43,040 --> 00:20:45,570
Have you never said
something wrong online?

536
00:20:46,110 --> 00:20:49,140
Never done something stupid
when you were younger?

537
00:20:50,240 --> 00:20:51,980
She's a good person.

538
00:20:52,030 --> 00:20:53,290
Bright, positive,

539
00:20:53,310 --> 00:20:54,700
kind, and brave.

540
00:20:55,270 --> 00:20:56,940
But you take a few out-of-context lines

541
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:57,940
and turn her

542
00:20:58,200 --> 00:21:00,810
into some arrogant, shallow gold-digger.

543
00:21:01,520 --> 00:21:03,220
You're just dumping

544
00:21:03,510 --> 00:21:05,570
your own frustrations on her.

545
00:21:07,720 --> 00:21:09,940
Well said, Yan Bowen.

546
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:49,900
Xiaoyan.

547
00:21:59,110 --> 00:22:00,090
Xiaoyan.

548
00:22:00,920 --> 00:22:01,660
Xiaoyan.

549
00:22:34,720 --> 00:22:35,490
Hello, Zhang Yu?

550
00:22:35,960 --> 00:22:36,730
Mentor,

551
00:22:37,030 --> 00:22:38,250
Xiaoyan's gone.

552
00:22:39,040 --> 00:22:40,620
Xiaoyan's gone?

553
00:22:41,310 --> 00:22:42,090
What happened?

554
00:22:42,440 --> 00:22:43,290
I have no idea.

555
00:22:43,790 --> 00:22:46,810
She reposted
that customs statement last night

556
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:48,180
and got doxed.

557
00:22:48,240 --> 00:22:49,770
People were cussing her out.

558
00:22:50,350 --> 00:22:51,330
I'm worried…

559
00:22:52,480 --> 00:22:53,980
Maybe she went home?

560
00:22:54,760 --> 00:22:57,530
She hasn't been getting along
with her parents lately.

561
00:22:57,550 --> 00:22:59,010
Just moved in with me.

562
00:22:59,110 --> 00:23:00,730
I don't think so.

563
00:23:01,790 --> 00:23:03,010
I'm back.

564
00:23:04,350 --> 00:23:06,420
Mom, I'll call you later, okay, bye.

565
00:23:11,750 --> 00:23:14,140
What's this, my wake-up call?

566
00:23:16,440 --> 00:23:18,140
I bought you breakfast,

567
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:20,770
shrimp dumplings,
congee, and rice rolls.

568
00:23:20,790 --> 00:23:21,810
Eat while it's hot.

569
00:23:21,830 --> 00:23:23,460
Boy, those breakfast stalls are busy

570
00:23:23,520 --> 00:23:25,490
in the morning.

571
00:23:26,680 --> 00:23:29,050
Where did you go?

572
00:23:29,070 --> 00:23:30,460
I went for a run.

573
00:23:31,110 --> 00:23:32,330
I'm gonna take a shower.

574
00:23:35,720 --> 00:23:37,090
You and your mom seem close,

575
00:23:37,110 --> 00:23:38,290
calling her first thing in the morning.

576
00:23:40,310 --> 00:23:42,900
She ran into a neighbor
on her morning walk

577
00:23:42,960 --> 00:23:44,940
and ended up talking about me.

578
00:23:45,720 --> 00:23:47,140
Alright, eat before it gets cold.

579
00:23:47,200 --> 00:23:47,980
I'll go shower.

580
00:23:48,520 --> 00:23:48,940
Okay.

581
00:23:53,030 --> 00:23:54,900
Serial number 001, worth 800,000 euros.

582
00:23:54,960 --> 00:23:56,050
It passed through
this gentleman's hands.

583
00:23:56,480 --> 00:23:57,330
This watch, what do you think?

584
00:23:58,960 --> 00:23:59,530
Three hundred thousand.

585
00:24:00,200 --> 00:24:01,290
Her salary?

586
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:02,460
In one month,

587
00:24:02,750 --> 00:24:04,770
she could probably buy dozens of those.

588
00:24:05,590 --> 00:24:08,050
Maybe even more.

589
00:24:10,030 --> 00:24:11,010
And you are…?

590
00:24:11,830 --> 00:24:12,900
My last name is Song.

591
00:24:13,040 --> 00:24:14,220
I'm a lawyer.

592
00:24:15,590 --> 00:24:17,090
I came to see you

593
00:24:17,240 --> 00:24:18,420
because I'm certain

594
00:24:18,480 --> 00:24:20,900
the Richard Mille watch in that video

595
00:24:21,280 --> 00:24:22,490
is the one you recently acquired

596
00:24:22,510 --> 00:24:24,290
at a European auction.

597
00:24:26,520 --> 00:24:27,250
That's right.

598
00:24:28,030 --> 00:24:29,290
But after duties,

599
00:24:29,510 --> 00:24:31,250
it cost more than
what the video claimed.

600
00:24:31,440 --> 00:24:31,810
Right.

601
00:24:33,280 --> 00:24:34,380
My client

602
00:24:34,440 --> 00:24:36,660
is also a collector of high-end watches.

603
00:24:37,240 --> 00:24:38,620
Too bad

604
00:24:38,720 --> 00:24:41,730
every piece he's wanted,
you got to first.

605
00:24:43,590 --> 00:24:45,290
But he doesn't see you

606
00:24:45,510 --> 00:24:47,570
as competition.

607
00:24:48,480 --> 00:24:49,860
Because, in his words,

608
00:24:50,070 --> 00:24:52,250
you share a common enemy.

609
00:24:53,680 --> 00:24:54,330
Enemy?

610
00:24:58,920 --> 00:24:59,620
Have a seat.

611
00:25:12,510 --> 00:25:13,730
You mean…

612
00:25:14,480 --> 00:25:15,490
China Customs?

613
00:25:15,590 --> 00:25:16,290
That's right.

614
00:25:19,750 --> 00:25:20,900
A lot of luxury watches

615
00:25:20,920 --> 00:25:22,940
get stuck overseas

616
00:25:23,110 --> 00:25:25,090
because of the high import duties,

617
00:25:25,480 --> 00:25:26,490
which is why

618
00:25:26,920 --> 00:25:28,180
he'd like to invite you

619
00:25:28,200 --> 00:25:30,460
to work together.

620
00:25:31,070 --> 00:25:32,220
As a gesture of goodwill,

621
00:25:32,790 --> 00:25:34,050
we produced that video,

622
00:25:34,510 --> 00:25:36,050
edited it carefully,

623
00:25:36,070 --> 00:25:37,290
and put it online.

624
00:25:37,720 --> 00:25:38,220
And now,

625
00:25:38,240 --> 00:25:40,460
public opinion is turning against them.

626
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:42,380
Consider it

627
00:25:43,270 --> 00:25:45,090
a way to help you get even, Mr. Zheng.

628
00:25:47,680 --> 00:25:48,940
So I believe,

629
00:25:49,270 --> 00:25:50,050
when the time comes,

630
00:25:50,070 --> 00:25:51,940
you'll be willing to cooperate with us

631
00:25:52,480 --> 00:25:54,010
and make them pay a price.

632
00:26:02,030 --> 00:26:03,050
Of course.

633
00:26:09,270 --> 00:26:10,090
Pleasure working with you.

634
00:26:10,840 --> 00:26:13,760
[CHINA CUSTOMS]

635
00:26:13,760 --> 00:26:17,400
[GOODS TO DECLARE
NOTHING TO DECLARE]

636
00:26:23,790 --> 00:26:24,380
Hello.

637
00:26:28,160 --> 00:26:29,700
Why do you keep staring at me?

638
00:26:29,830 --> 00:26:31,730
Because you're looking at me.

639
00:26:34,310 --> 00:26:35,420
I know why Mr. Guo asked you

640
00:26:35,440 --> 00:26:36,860
to stick with me today.

641
00:26:36,960 --> 00:26:39,140
He's worried I'll lose my cool
and get bullied.

642
00:26:39,830 --> 00:26:41,380
But he overestimated you.

643
00:26:41,960 --> 00:26:43,900
He doesn't know
you didn't call the police

644
00:26:43,920 --> 00:26:45,010
when someone threw bugs at you.

645
00:26:45,640 --> 00:26:46,700
That was not the same.

646
00:26:47,110 --> 00:26:49,090
I'm on duty now.

647
00:26:49,160 --> 00:26:49,700
I'm not going

648
00:26:49,720 --> 00:26:51,140
to embarrass our section.

649
00:26:51,350 --> 00:26:51,980
Okay.

650
00:26:52,350 --> 00:26:53,860
If I get into a fight later,

651
00:26:53,880 --> 00:26:54,940
you'd better come help me.

652
00:26:56,240 --> 00:26:57,050
That's not a good idea.

653
00:26:57,680 --> 00:26:58,940
Look at you, nervous already.

654
00:26:59,240 --> 00:27:00,220
Relax.

655
00:27:00,310 --> 00:27:01,900
I'll watch what I say and do.

656
00:27:01,960 --> 00:27:02,900
I'll not give anyone

657
00:27:02,920 --> 00:27:04,090
a reason to smear us.

658
00:27:04,640 --> 00:27:05,980
I hope so.

659
00:27:07,960 --> 00:27:08,810
What was that?

660
00:27:10,310 --> 00:27:11,460
Hello, China Customs.

661
00:27:11,510 --> 00:27:12,660
Please use the lane to your left.

662
00:27:12,680 --> 00:27:13,220
Thank you.

663
00:27:16,920 --> 00:27:17,290
I didn't say anything.

664
00:27:18,480 --> 00:27:19,180
Yeah, right.

665
00:27:26,480 --> 00:27:29,460
Ma'am, the total value
of these skincare products

666
00:27:29,480 --> 00:27:31,090
exceeds the duty-free limit.

667
00:27:31,160 --> 00:27:32,250
Please come with me

668
00:27:32,270 --> 00:27:33,570
to pay the additional tax.

669
00:27:34,350 --> 00:27:35,460
Can't you make an exception?

670
00:27:35,480 --> 00:27:37,010
It's not that much over.

671
00:27:37,350 --> 00:27:39,770
This one set alone
already exceeds the limit,

672
00:27:39,790 --> 00:27:41,330
and you're carrying two.

673
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:44,940
Ma'am, please open your bag.

674
00:27:44,960 --> 00:27:45,860
You…

675
00:27:46,510 --> 00:27:47,900
You're that ostentatious

676
00:27:47,920 --> 00:27:50,420
customs girl from online, aren't you?

677
00:27:50,640 --> 00:27:51,810
Pay the additional tax?

678
00:27:52,030 --> 00:27:54,250
Do you plan to keep it for yourself

679
00:27:54,270 --> 00:27:55,660
or resell it and pocket the cash?

680
00:27:55,720 --> 00:27:56,330
Ma'am,

681
00:27:56,440 --> 00:27:57,730
whatever I do online

682
00:27:57,750 --> 00:27:59,050
and in my personal life

683
00:27:59,110 --> 00:28:01,420
has nothing to do
with whether you owe duty.

684
00:28:01,480 --> 00:28:03,050
Please cooperate with the inspection

685
00:28:03,070 --> 00:28:04,660
and don't hold up the line.

686
00:28:06,160 --> 00:28:07,620
Those comments

687
00:28:07,640 --> 00:28:08,660
really got a point.

688
00:28:08,750 --> 00:28:09,980
Die, trash.

689
00:28:10,070 --> 00:28:11,730
Please watch your language.

690
00:28:11,750 --> 00:28:13,770
Insulting an officer on duty

691
00:28:13,790 --> 00:28:15,660
can carry legal consequences.

692
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:17,620
Those are not my words.

693
00:28:18,480 --> 00:28:19,250
Fine. Alright.

694
00:28:22,830 --> 00:28:24,420
Please come with me.

695
00:28:25,160 --> 00:28:26,620
Hello, please open your bag.

696
00:28:34,240 --> 00:28:36,220
Xiaoyan seems a lot calmer today.

697
00:28:36,350 --> 00:28:37,050
Yeah.

698
00:28:37,550 --> 00:28:39,490
Like a completely
different person overnight.

699
00:28:39,790 --> 00:28:40,860
Please open it yourself.

700
00:28:47,590 --> 00:28:48,220
Mr. Guo.

701
00:28:49,070 --> 00:28:50,050
Copy that.

702
00:28:52,590 --> 00:28:53,530
Checked?

703
00:28:56,270 --> 00:28:57,050
Zhang Yu.

704
00:28:57,680 --> 00:28:59,730
Check that woman
with the black backpack.

705
00:28:59,750 --> 00:29:00,420
Green suitcase.

706
00:29:00,680 --> 00:29:01,220
Hello,

707
00:29:02,200 --> 00:29:02,860
please open your bag.

708
00:29:04,440 --> 00:29:05,220
Hello?

709
00:29:05,880 --> 00:29:06,730
Okay, hold on.

710
00:29:08,920 --> 00:29:09,810
Mr. Guo,

711
00:29:10,240 --> 00:29:11,010
take this call.

712
00:29:17,790 --> 00:29:18,900
Hello, this is Guo Cong.

713
00:29:20,030 --> 00:29:20,770
Yes, go ahead.

714
00:29:24,070 --> 00:29:24,980
Okay, understood.

715
00:29:26,790 --> 00:29:27,570
Thank you.

716
00:29:36,790 --> 00:29:37,810
Who was it?

717
00:29:38,030 --> 00:29:39,330
No idea. He's gone.

718
00:29:52,590 --> 00:29:53,290
Hello?

719
00:30:01,680 --> 00:30:02,380
What?

720
00:30:04,200 --> 00:30:04,700
Okay…

721
00:30:05,200 --> 00:30:06,050
Okay, got it.

722
00:30:12,920 --> 00:30:13,460
Thanks.

723
00:30:16,750 --> 00:30:17,330
I'll handle this.

724
00:30:17,520 --> 00:30:18,250
It's fine, Yu.

725
00:30:18,270 --> 00:30:19,220
To me, he's just

726
00:30:19,280 --> 00:30:20,220
another passenger

727
00:30:20,280 --> 00:30:21,380
going through inspection.

728
00:30:23,110 --> 00:30:23,770
Okay.

729
00:30:29,030 --> 00:30:30,180
Hello, China Customs.

730
00:30:30,550 --> 00:30:32,140
Please come here for inspection.

731
00:30:34,590 --> 00:30:35,530
You're checking this too?

732
00:30:35,720 --> 00:30:36,980
These are my personal belongings.

733
00:30:37,520 --> 00:30:39,420
This bracelet appears to be agarwood.

734
00:30:39,480 --> 00:30:40,460
Under customs regulations,

735
00:30:40,520 --> 00:30:42,220
agarwood is a protected species.

736
00:30:42,270 --> 00:30:44,290
You need proper permits

737
00:30:44,520 --> 00:30:46,620
to bring it in or out of the country.

738
00:30:46,680 --> 00:30:48,530
Please provide the documentation.

739
00:30:50,280 --> 00:30:51,700
That's a first.

740
00:30:51,960 --> 00:30:54,660
I've seen plenty of people wear these.
No one stops them.

741
00:30:54,720 --> 00:30:55,730
Why me?

742
00:30:56,200 --> 00:30:57,490
Sir, it's not about you.

743
00:30:57,510 --> 00:30:59,090
Anything that may be restricted

744
00:30:59,110 --> 00:31:00,010
gets checked.

745
00:31:10,760 --> 00:31:11,660
I recognize you.

746
00:31:12,040 --> 00:31:13,250
You're one of my fans, right?

747
00:31:13,920 --> 00:31:15,940
The one who's been trending online…

748
00:31:16,510 --> 00:31:17,860
Strawberry something?

749
00:31:18,480 --> 00:31:19,380
What do you want?

750
00:31:19,830 --> 00:31:20,530
An autograph?

751
00:31:20,680 --> 00:31:22,090
Sir, no matter who you are,

752
00:31:22,270 --> 00:31:24,660
you still have to follow
customs regulations.

753
00:31:29,480 --> 00:31:31,330
So this is you trying
to get my attention?

754
00:31:31,760 --> 00:31:33,090
Are you using your position

755
00:31:33,240 --> 00:31:35,730
to fangirl over me?

756
00:31:36,270 --> 00:31:37,730
I've seen your type before.

757
00:31:37,830 --> 00:31:39,530
Living in their own fantasy,

758
00:31:39,750 --> 00:31:41,860
thinking they can get close
to their idols.

759
00:31:43,200 --> 00:31:43,770
Sir,

760
00:31:44,070 --> 00:31:45,330
I'll remind you one more time.

761
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:48,010
Bringing agarwood
across the border without documentation

762
00:31:48,110 --> 00:31:49,380
may constitute smuggling.

763
00:31:49,830 --> 00:31:50,420
Also,

764
00:31:51,030 --> 00:31:52,380
as a public figure,

765
00:31:52,830 --> 00:31:54,490
you should be mindful of your behavior.

766
00:31:54,680 --> 00:31:56,660
Set a better example

767
00:31:56,750 --> 00:31:57,940
for the people who look up to you.

768
00:31:59,240 --> 00:32:00,810
These pretty-boy celebrities these days,

769
00:32:00,830 --> 00:32:02,490
all style, no substance.

770
00:32:02,790 --> 00:32:03,530
They think

771
00:32:03,550 --> 00:32:05,090
the world revolves around them.

772
00:32:05,510 --> 00:32:06,090
Ridiculous.

773
00:32:07,030 --> 00:32:08,700
Now, Mr. Fan Zitian,

774
00:32:09,070 --> 00:32:10,660
please come with me

775
00:32:10,790 --> 00:32:12,490
for further inspection.

776
00:32:21,550 --> 00:32:22,330
Excuse me.

777
00:32:25,040 --> 00:32:26,050
Please open your luggage.

778
00:32:26,070 --> 00:32:27,490
Wei, come help Zhang Yu.

779
00:32:44,310 --> 00:32:45,140
Done. Thank you.

780
00:32:45,720 --> 00:32:47,250
When Fan Zitian said that earlier,

781
00:32:47,270 --> 00:32:48,900
I thought you'd snap back at him.

782
00:32:49,680 --> 00:32:50,860
Back in the day,

783
00:32:50,920 --> 00:32:52,700
I would've torn him apart.

784
00:32:52,960 --> 00:32:53,940
But not anymore.

785
00:32:54,200 --> 00:32:56,140
We represent customs now.

786
00:32:56,240 --> 00:32:58,900
I can't afford to lose my temper.

787
00:33:00,000 --> 00:33:02,290
Wow… People really do change.

788
00:33:02,440 --> 00:33:03,570
Guess the old saying's true.

789
00:33:04,920 --> 00:33:07,250
I can't let down the people online
who support me

790
00:33:07,270 --> 00:33:08,980
and believe in customs.

791
00:33:09,040 --> 00:33:09,530
Right?

792
00:33:17,760 --> 00:33:18,700
Where's Mr. Guo?

793
00:33:25,750 --> 00:33:26,460
Wei.

794
00:33:26,520 --> 00:33:27,380
Cover for me a second.

795
00:33:29,760 --> 00:33:30,180
China Customs.

796
00:33:30,240 --> 00:33:31,770
- Please open your luggage.
- I'll go check on him.

797
00:33:39,310 --> 00:33:40,250
What's wrong, Mentor?

798
00:33:40,790 --> 00:33:41,730
What happened?

799
00:33:42,030 --> 00:33:43,530
The nursing home called.

800
00:33:43,790 --> 00:33:45,810
My mentor collapsed from heart failure.

801
00:33:46,200 --> 00:33:47,180
They just revived him.

802
00:33:47,830 --> 00:33:49,220
Then go see him.

803
00:33:49,920 --> 00:33:51,290
It's okay,
we've got things covered here.

804
00:33:53,040 --> 00:33:54,980
Customs is under
a lot of pressure right now.

805
00:33:55,070 --> 00:33:56,140
I can't just take leave.

806
00:33:56,480 --> 00:33:57,620
I've already called Uncle Xiang.

807
00:33:57,680 --> 00:33:58,530
He's on his way.

808
00:33:59,350 --> 00:33:59,860
Let's go.

809
00:34:01,950 --> 00:34:03,180
Mentor, don't worry.

810
00:34:03,320 --> 00:34:04,540
We can go see him after our shift.

811
00:34:04,600 --> 00:34:05,050
Okay.

812
00:34:06,560 --> 00:34:06,940
Go.

813
00:34:08,480 --> 00:34:10,570
So what's Chen's condition right now?

814
00:34:11,070 --> 00:34:13,570
His physical condition
has been declining rapidly.

815
00:34:14,040 --> 00:34:15,610
He had acute heart failure today.

816
00:34:16,040 --> 00:34:17,090
But they managed to stabilize him.

817
00:34:17,190 --> 00:34:17,860
Good.

818
00:34:18,190 --> 00:34:19,460
Do you think I should

819
00:34:19,520 --> 00:34:20,820
transfer him to another hospital

820
00:34:20,880 --> 00:34:21,740
for further treatment?

821
00:34:21,800 --> 00:34:22,610
I can arrange that.

822
00:34:22,880 --> 00:34:23,340
Xiang,

823
00:34:23,400 --> 00:34:24,820
I need to tell you something.

824
00:34:24,880 --> 00:34:25,380
Go ahead.

825
00:34:25,800 --> 00:34:28,740
Chen is showing signs
of terminal lucidity.

826
00:34:29,040 --> 00:34:29,780
What does that mean?

827
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:33,570
It's a phenomenon
medicine still can't fully explain.

828
00:34:33,710 --> 00:34:35,900
Patients with Alzheimer's

829
00:34:36,040 --> 00:34:37,210
sometimes suddenly

830
00:34:37,230 --> 00:34:38,980
regain clarity near the end of life.

831
00:34:39,070 --> 00:34:40,420
They can communicate normally again.

832
00:34:40,670 --> 00:34:43,420
In the medical field abroad,
this is called

833
00:34:43,480 --> 00:34:45,090
terminal lucidity.

834
00:34:45,230 --> 00:34:46,050
A brief return

835
00:34:46,280 --> 00:34:47,460
of awareness at the end.

836
00:34:49,360 --> 00:34:50,650
Like a final rally?

837
00:34:51,920 --> 00:34:53,460
Something like that.

838
00:34:57,510 --> 00:34:58,210
Director Huang,

839
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:01,210
how much time does he have left?

840
00:35:04,760 --> 00:35:05,610
Hard to say.

841
00:35:06,960 --> 00:35:07,940
Maybe a few days.

842
00:35:08,800 --> 00:35:10,300
Maybe just a few hours.

843
00:35:10,550 --> 00:35:11,380
Could be either.

844
00:35:16,440 --> 00:35:16,980
Okay.

845
00:35:17,630 --> 00:35:18,420
I'll go see him.

846
00:35:19,000 --> 00:35:19,690
Thank you.

847
00:35:35,080 --> 00:35:43,200
[CHINA CUSTOMS
CUSTOMS INSPECTION]

848
00:35:48,920 --> 00:35:50,440
[Binhai Aviation Catering Company]

849
00:35:50,440 --> 00:35:52,160
[Binhai Airlines]

850
00:35:52,160 --> 00:35:53,120
[CHINA CUSTOMS]

851
00:36:08,150 --> 00:36:10,210
Right face.

852
00:36:12,230 --> 00:36:13,650
All units!

853
00:36:14,150 --> 00:36:15,610
Prepare for shift handover.

854
00:36:16,070 --> 00:36:17,050
Salute!

855
00:36:19,030 --> 00:36:19,980
Order arms!

856
00:36:20,710 --> 00:36:21,380
Section II,

857
00:36:22,000 --> 00:36:23,010
everyone

858
00:36:23,590 --> 00:36:24,260
except Wang Wenlei,

859
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:25,780
report to your posts.

860
00:36:25,800 --> 00:36:27,530
Yes, sir!

861
00:36:38,190 --> 00:36:38,980
Cong,

862
00:36:41,070 --> 00:36:41,940
your mentor

863
00:36:43,880 --> 00:36:44,650
is gone.

864
00:36:48,110 --> 00:36:49,740
Let's give Comrade Chen Sanhe

865
00:36:49,840 --> 00:36:51,260
a final salute.

866
00:37:11,400 --> 00:37:13,130
All units!

867
00:37:14,070 --> 00:37:15,610
Salute!

868
00:37:37,160 --> 00:37:48,560
[CHINA CUSTOMS]

869
00:38:18,550 --> 00:38:19,170
Mentor,

870
00:38:20,760 --> 00:38:21,820
I'll drive.

871
00:38:52,760 --> 00:38:53,420
Cong.

872
00:39:38,360 --> 00:39:39,740
Mentor!

873
00:39:45,710 --> 00:39:46,940
Mentor…

874
00:39:53,030 --> 00:39:53,980
Mentor…

875
00:41:09,960 --> 00:41:11,490
I suddenly thought of my dad…

876
00:41:13,150 --> 00:41:14,530
Haven't in a long time.

877
00:41:16,400 --> 00:41:17,420
I remember

878
00:41:17,960 --> 00:41:19,300
the last time I saw him,

879
00:41:19,760 --> 00:41:21,090
[Xiangliang]
they were carrying him off the ship.

880
00:41:21,090 --> 00:41:21,880
[Xiangliang]

881
00:41:29,070 --> 00:41:29,690
Shuliang!

882
00:41:30,670 --> 00:41:31,530
Shuliang!

883
00:41:35,400 --> 00:41:36,380
His hands

884
00:41:36,880 --> 00:41:37,820
were so pale.

885
00:41:38,550 --> 00:41:39,260
So pale

886
00:41:40,110 --> 00:41:41,380
that it didn't even look real.

887
00:41:41,880 --> 00:41:42,980
Shuliang!

888
00:41:45,000 --> 00:41:46,490
Shuliang!

889
00:41:47,590 --> 00:41:48,860
Dad…

890
00:41:58,630 --> 00:41:59,650
Cong.

891
00:41:59,960 --> 00:42:01,130
Here, have some water.

892
00:42:11,400 --> 00:42:11,940
Uncle Xiang,

893
00:42:13,480 --> 00:42:14,570
do take care of yourself.

894
00:42:15,960 --> 00:42:16,820
Now,

895
00:42:17,880 --> 00:42:18,980
you're all I have.

896
00:42:22,710 --> 00:42:23,740
Don't be silly.

897
00:42:25,510 --> 00:42:27,530
You still have your mom to look after.

898
00:42:28,360 --> 00:42:29,900
You need to stay strong.

899
00:42:34,590 --> 00:42:37,170
Your mentor held on for three years

900
00:42:37,480 --> 00:42:38,940
after the accident.

901
00:42:39,480 --> 00:42:41,530
You could say he stayed
those extra years for you.

902
00:42:45,320 --> 00:42:46,260
He was tired.

903
00:42:47,000 --> 00:42:48,130
Let him go.

904
00:42:49,960 --> 00:42:51,260
Just remember him.

905
00:43:30,800 --> 00:43:37,360
♪There's a place of simple,
everyday warmth♪

906
00:43:38,280 --> 00:43:45,000
♪A door left open
for the wandering soul♪

907
00:43:45,920 --> 00:43:52,440
♪A humble table still warm with love♪

908
00:43:52,680 --> 00:43:56,320
♪After you've tasted every high and low♪

909
00:43:56,600 --> 00:44:00,240
♪Come home, I'll keep you warm♪

910
00:44:01,000 --> 00:44:07,680
♪Where the days begin and end♪

911
00:44:08,400 --> 00:44:15,320
♪A light still on for the ones
who've lost their way♪

912
00:44:16,120 --> 00:44:22,680
♪An embrace waiting just for you♪

913
00:44:22,960 --> 00:44:26,680
♪Through every passing season♪

914
00:44:26,800 --> 00:44:30,480
♪Even if you return with nothing at all♪

915
00:44:31,120 --> 00:44:34,600
♪Turn around and look♪

916
00:44:34,800 --> 00:44:38,600
♪That door's still open♪

917
00:44:38,800 --> 00:44:42,440
♪A light still burning♪

918
00:44:42,520 --> 00:44:46,240
♪Waiting there for you♪

919
00:44:46,400 --> 00:44:49,920
♪Turn around and look♪

920
00:44:50,160 --> 00:44:53,960
♪Someone's still waiting♪

921
00:44:54,160 --> 00:44:57,760
♪Watching the dusk settle in♪

922
00:44:57,840 --> 00:45:01,560
♪Waiting for the break of dawn♪

923
00:45:03,320 --> 00:45:06,960
♪It's always there♪
